{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"117ecfdc-a242-4f76-8fc9-2b7f3ad52737","content":"## The Problem\n\n**.NET 9+ Android builds require JDK 21**, but you only have JDK 17 installed. The build likely fails with an error like:\n\n> `Java SDK 21.0 or above is required when using .NET 9`\n\n## The Fix\n\nInstall JDK 21 and update `JAVA_HOME`:\n\n```bash\nbrew install --cask temurin@21\nexport JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home\n```\n\nAdd the `export` line to your `~/.zshrc` (or `~/.bash_profile`) to persist it.\n\nAlternatively, you can set it per-project in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <JavaSdkDirectory>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-21.jdk/Contents/Home</JavaSdkDirectory>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**TL;DR** — .NET 8 needed JDK 17; .NET 9+ needs JDK 21. Upgrade your JDK.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"486d5c68-bd7b-4307-b372-9af1d9291c90","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed with JAVA_HOME pointing to it.\n\nThis is a common issue with .NET MAUI Android builds. The problem is likely that .NET MAUI / Android SDK requires a specific Java version, and the way JAVA_HOME is set on macOS with Adoptium Temurin can sometimes be incorrect.\n\nLet me think about common issues:\n\n1. **.NET 8+ MAUI requires JDK 17** - they have JDK 17, so that's fine.\n\n\n2. **JAVA_HOME path on macOS** - On macOS, Adoptium Temurin installs to `/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`, and the user needs to verify JAVA_HOME points to the correct location.\n3. **MSBuild property mismatch** - The .NET Android SDK has its own `$(JavaSdkDirectory)` property that might not respect JAVA_HOME or could be conflicting with it.\n\nThe most common Java-related error with .NET MAUI Android builds typically stems from one of these configuration issues.\n\nActually, I should reconsider the JDK version requirements. .NET 8 MAUI requires JDK 17, but .NET 9 MAUI bumped the minimum requirement to JDK 17 as well, though there might be some nuance around whether it prefers JDK 21. Let me think through the version matrix: .NET 7 needs JDK 11, .NET 8 needs JDK 17, and .NET 9 maintains JDK 17 as the minimum. not entirely sure about the exact version cutoffs. For .NET 9, I believe the Android workload bumped the requirement to JDK 21, and the error message would likely indicate that Java SDK 21 or above is needed. The solution would be installing JDK 21, setting the JAVA_HOME environment variable to point to it, or configuring the JavaSdkDirectory property in the project file.","outputTokens":1284,"requestId":"D444:7818E:1D1063F:20A41CF:6A07C177"},"id":"16acfbb7-c72e-40e9-a88f-acf9aafd2e29","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:59:57.695Z","parentId":"d1d93d38-abaf-450d-a236-39f99f7b6a3d"}
